# Content Pipeline Loop (Strict)

Use when remediating one or more blog articles. Run steps in order; do not skip.

1. Ensure `temp_articles_checklist.txt` exists (one `- [ ] src/content/blog/<slug>.mdx` per article).
2. **Keywords assignment** — follow `content-keywords-assignment-loop.mdc` (`mainKeyword`, 4-6 `secondaryKeywords`, `contentType`).
3. **Research** — `pnpm run research:scaffold -- <slug>` (if missing) → `article-research-loop.mdc` (fetch, ≥2000w study, set `research_completed_at`) → `pnpm run research:audit -- <slug>`; delete study only after scoped `content:audit` passes.
4. **Content type** — confirm `pillar` vs `cluster` matches `getArticleTier(slug)`.
5. **Content enhancer** — follow `content-enhancer-loop.mdc` (26-rule checklist, keywords before prose; research audit must pass first).
6. **E-E-A-T structure** — follow `content-eeat-structure-loop.mdc` (TL;DR, FAQ, stats, CTA, external sources).
7. **Pillar-cluster links** — follow `internal-links-pillar-cluster-loop.mdc` (intent pathway + cornerstone equity).
8. **Internal links** — follow `internal-links-loop.mdc` (10 paragraph links; 3-5 topical blog + hubs; optional `linkGoal` in frontmatter).
9. **Homepage brand link** — follow `homepage-brand-internal-links-loop.mdc`.
10. **FAQ/schema check** — frontmatter `faq` or body `## שאלות נפוצות`; FAQPage JSON-LD when >=4 items.
11. Run `pnpm run verify:content` (`CONTENT_AUDIT_SLUGS=<slug>`). On failure, log `ERROR` with slug and fix before marking done.
12. Optional strict gate: `CONTENT_STRICT=1 CONTENT_AUDIT_SLUGS=<slug> pnpm run content:audit`.
13. Run `pnpm run image-keyword-compliance` when images changed.
14. Run `pnpm run links:audit` (`LINKS_AUDIT_ENFORCE=1` before merge when graph must be clean).
14b. Optional full rule matrix: `LINKS_AUDIT_FULL=1 pnpm run links:audit:full` (61-rule PASS/FAIL/MANUAL report).
15. Run `pnpm run seo:guardrails` (`CONTENT_AUDIT_ENFORCE=1`; `CONTENT_LINKS_STRICT=1` for anchor rules).
16. Run `pnpm run build:ci`.
17. Mark article `[x]` in all checklists when steps 2-16 pass for that slug.

Hard requirements:
- Research files only under `.cursor/tmp/research/<slug>.md`; delete only after dual audit (research + content).
- Scoped pipeline runs set `REQUIRE_RESEARCH=1` automatically (`scripts/run-content-pipeline.mjs`).
- Preserve frontmatter schema in `src/lib/content/schema.ts`; new fields optional for legacy posts.
- Log each step: `[content-pipeline-loop] step N: ...` or `[content-pipeline-loop] ERROR ...`.

## Env flags
| Flag | Effect |
|------|--------|
| `REQUIRE_RESEARCH=1` | Preflight fails if study missing or invalid |
| `RESEARCH_AUDIT_SLUGS` | Scoped research audit in verify / CI |
| `RESEARCH_MIN_DURATION_SEC` | Optional override for tests only |
| `CONTENT_AUDIT_ENFORCE=1` | CI article audit via seo:guardrails |
| `CONTENT_LINKS_STRICT=1` | Anchor, section, cannibalization, first-100w keyword |
| `CONTENT_STRICT=1` | Full 2026 rules (LSI, FAQ, TL;DR, metaDesc max 155, etc.) |
| `LINKS_AUDIT_ENFORCE=1` | Orphan graph enforcement |
| `LINKS_AUDIT_FULL=1` | Append `links:audit:full` in verify:content (61-rule matrix) |
